            </figure>

            <div data-toc-linked id="outputs" class="cs:chunk">
                {{ elements.csTitle('h3', 'Outputs') }}
                <div class="cs:content">
                    <p>
                        During Mike's seven months at Abstract, Mike built a new content-hub <span class="italic color:ink-1">(design + dev)</span>, rebuilt the homepage <span class="italic color:ink-1">(design + dev)</span>, created an all new set of product pages <span class="italic color:ink-1">(design + dev)</span>, designed a new sign-up experience, and designed a handful of other marketings assets such as ads and blog graphics.
                    </p>
                    <ul class="relative flex flex:col gap:32 md:gap:48 w:100p">
                        <li class="flex flex:col gap:8 w:100p pl:20 sm:pl:32 border-l:1 border:primary-rg">
                            <h4 class="font:md sm:font:lg color:ink-3 mt:n8">
                                Content Hub: In the Margin
                            </h4>
                            <p class="font:sm sm:font:md color:ink-1">
                                In an effort to drive brand engagement, generate leads, and solidify Abstract's position as a leader in the space, In the Margin was born. Mike was tasked with finding an intuitive way to integrate content from the blog, podcast, and external contributors into the new site while also creating a fresh sub-brand for the property. Mike lead both the design and development of this project. He worked closely with community and growth marketers.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex flex:col gap:8 w:100p pl:20 sm:pl:32 border-l:1 border:primary-rg">
                            <h4 class="font:md sm:font:lg color:ink-3 mt:n8">
                                Redesign: Homepage
                            </h4>
                            <p class="font:sm sm:font:md color:ink-1 mb:n4">
                                Prior to Mike joining, Abstract's core product was their Sketch version control tool. Mike joined the team during the pivot to the new product, Notebooks, which meant updating the marketing properties to reflect this all new tool. In the end, Mike created a beautifully crafted new homepage that was featured by multiple sites, including Webflow itself.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex flex:col gap:8 w:100p pl:20 sm:pl:32 border-l:1 border:primary-rg">
                            <h4 class="font:md sm:font:lg color:ink-3 mt:n8">
                                Redesign: Product Sign-up
                            </h4>
                            <p class="font:sm sm:font:md color:ink-1 mb:n4">
                                Between the two products at Abstract, the product design team had their hands full. Due to this, and the fact that marketing lead most top-of-funnel projects, Mike was asked to help design a new signup experience for the product that increased conversion. Working between marketing, brand, product, and engineering â€“ Mike took a once sterile sign-up process to the next level by adding delight, messaging, and simplicity to the flow.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

