            <div data-toc-linked id="takeaways" class="cs:chunk">
                {{ elements.csTitle('h3', 'Takeaways') }}
                <div class="cs:content">
                    <p>
                        As mentioned earlier, Adobe acquired Notebooks in Nov. 2021 ðŸ¥². Abstract was the the first role that Mike worked inhouse in "tech" rather than on an agency/freelance basis.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        He found working inhouse to be an absolute delight. At agencies, the engagements are extremely fast paced, having the ability to get deeply familiar with a product while designing for it is priceless. With that, having access to every team <span class="italic color:ink-1">(not just marketing)</span> made gaining a deep understanding of the product that much easier.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Being able to participate in the strategy, direction, and prioritization process vs. only getting called once a solution has been decided upon was satisfying, and seemingly lead to better outcomes than the latter.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Abstract helped Mike understand the affect of soft skills and, by example, how to purposefully lead with design to achieve greater results. Going forward, Mike has placed a higher focus on communicating and questioning the purpose, reasoning, and justification of projects to help ensure their impact.
                    </p>
